<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: SAN DIEGO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A La Mesa woman pleaded innocent Friday to abandoning her twin daughters at a 
shopping mall to avoid being arrested for shoplifting. 
</P>
<P>
Della Youngblood, 20, also is charged with petty theft, child abuse, and 
battery on a police officer. 
</P>
<P>
The battery charge stems from allegations that, when she drove off, her car 
struck the arm of a security guard at Fashion Valley. 
</P>
<P>
William Edwards, with the public defender's office, asked for a bail review 
June 27 after San Diego Municipal Court Judge Patricia Cowett set bail at 
$25,000. 
</P>
<P>
A preliminary hearing was scheduled for July 6. 
</P>
<P>
The 2-year-old girls were left in a shopping cart Tuesday and taken to 
Hillcrest Receiving Home. Edwards said Youngblood is pregnant, but he didn't 
know when her baby is due. 
</P>
</TEXT>
