<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRADER CLAIMS 1ST STREET STOCK MAIN-EVENT WIN AT VENTURA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By PAUL OLSON, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Lynn Brader of Somis drove to his first main-event win of the season in the 
Street Stock 15-lap race at Ventura Raceway on Friday night. 
</P>
<P>
Scott Olsen of Ventura led for six laps before he lost control and fishtailed 
in Turn 4, allowing Brader to overtake him. 
</P>
<P>
Olsen was second and Don Keeter of Ventura finished third and moved into the 
oval track season points lead over Jim Firsich of Port Hueneme. 
</P>
<P>
Pat Garrety of Oxnard also drove to his first main-event win of the season in 
the Mini Stock 20-lap race. 
</P>
<P>
Pat Davis of Port Hueneme had led for 13 laps before Garrety overtook him on 
the back straightaway. Marty Desbrow of Ventura finished second and Davis took 
third. 
</P>
<P>
With the aid of a yellow flag, Terry Swauger of Ojai drove to victory in the 
Mini Stock eight-lap figure-eight main event. Russ Warren of Van Nuys had just 
passed Swauger on Lap 5 when Port Hueneme contestant Joe Silva's car caught 
fire to bring out the yellow and put Swauger back on top; he then held on for 
the win. Warren was second and Forrest Nickerson of Santa Paula was third. 
</P>
<P>
Oxnard's Randy Gens drove to his first victory of the season, leading 
wire-to-wire in the Street Stock six-lap Figure-eight main event. Firsich was 
second and Olsen was third. 
</P>
