<HEADLINE>
<P>
RISE IN FRENCH CRIME IS BIGGEST IN 5 YEARS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
PARIS 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The crime rate in France rose by 4.27% in 1989, the first increase in five 
years, according to official figures published Friday. 
</P>
<P>
The rise was caused mostly by increases in drug offenses, car theft and 
offenses linked to illegal immigration, the police report said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
