METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: BRADLEY SIGNS HOUSING ORDINANCE INTO LAW 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Mayor Tom Bradley on Friday signed into law an ordinance creating a city 
Housing Preservation and Production Department and a Commission on Affordable 
Housing. 
</P>
<P>
The mayor's office announced earlier that the department would be formed so the 
city's housing programs could be centralized into a single agency with a 
mandate to analyze the affordable housing crisis and implement programs to 
provide more housing. 
</P>
<P>
"A comprehensive examination of housing issues in this city is necessary for us 
to address this problem that depletes the quality of life for too many Los 
Angeles residents," Bradley said. 
</P>
