</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
AIDS Education Week, sponsored by the Dionne Warwick Foundation, will begin 
Monday with a ministers conference on AIDS at the First African Methodist 
Episcopal Church in Los Angeles, organizers said. 
</P>
<P>
The conference will focus on creating a healthy response to the AIDS crisis 
within the church environment. More than 75 Los Angeles-area ministers are 
expected to participate in the conference, which runs from 9:30 to 11:30 a.m. 
</P>
<P>
The rest of the week will feature workshops at various locations on how AIDS is 
spread, an AIDS legislative update for health care professionals, a "rap" opera 
on AIDS and several other programs. 
