<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE: NAMES IN THE NEWS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Robert H. Lurie, part-owner of the Chicago White Sox and Chicago Bulls and 
among the nation's richest men, died of cancer. He was 48. Lurie, who was not 
related to Robert A. Lurie, owner of the San Francisco Giants, died at 
Chicago's Northwest Memorial Hospital. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Obituary 
</P>
