<HEADLINE>
<P>
CALIFORNIA IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
LOMA LINDA; 
</P>
<P>
GIRLS IN DESERT CASE REMAIN HOSPITALIZED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Two young girls found abandoned in the Mojave Desert six days after they 
disappeared with an adult family friend remained hospitalized Friday as San 
Bernardino sheriff's deputies continued to comb the Barstow area for the 
alleged abductor. 
</P>
<P>
Kristina Johnson, 3, of Pioneertown, was suffering from partial kidney failure 
and was in serious condition at Loma Linda University Medical Center. She also 
was being treated for dehydration and for minor scratches she apparently 
received when she fell down an embankment, a hospital spokeswoman said. 
Kristina's half-sister, Silver Putnam, 6, was in good condition at Barstow 
Community Hospital. A kidnaping arrest warrant was issued for Alan Erickson, 
36, of Pioneertown. 
</P>
</TEXT>
