<HEADLINE>
<P>
CALIFORNIA IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
ORANGE; 
</P>
<P>
TRW EMPLOYEE TIED TO CREDIT FRAUD RING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
U.S. Secret Service agents have uncovered a fraud ring that allegedly was 
funneling sensitive credit information out of TRW Credit Data Division, one of 
the nation's largest credit bureaus, authorities said Friday. 
</P>
<P>
Several sealed indictments have been obtained, according to the Secret Service, 
which is investigating the matter, but it was not revealed how soon the 
indictments will be made public. The ring reportedly involved a TRW employee 
who leaked credit information to outsiders. They, in turn, used the information 
to fraudulently obtain merchandise and for other illegal purposes. While both 
Secret Service and TRW officials confirmed an investigation was under way, they 
said they could not give any more details until the indictments are unsealed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
