<HEADLINE>
<P>
DECISION DELAYED IN RAPPAPORT CASE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Relatives of the late actor David Rappaport, who committed suicide last month 
and did not leave a will, must wait until July 20 to find out whether they will 
be able to wrest control of the entertainer's U.S. estate from Los Angeles 
County authorities. 
</P>
<P>
A Los Angeles Superior Court probate administrator on Friday put off a decision 
on the case until Frankie Leigh, Rappaport's manager and cousin, is formally 
appointed guardian of the actor's son and heir, Joseph. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
