<HEADLINE>
<P>
O.C. RELIGION NOTES / THUHA TRAN: UNITARIAN CHURCH POETRY READING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By THUHA TRAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Poetry reading by the congregation's poetry group will take place at 10:30 a.m. 
Sunday at the Orange Coast Unitarian Universalist Church, 1259 Victoria St., 
Costa Mesa. The program, conducted by Marsha Hudson of Huntington Beach, will 
consist of the reading of favorite poems and original works. Participants 
include Jean Brookhart of Huntington Beach; Jake Jaramillo of Costa Mesa; 
Margaret Gerard of Fountain Valley; Eleanor Tucker of Newport Beach; and 
Charlie and Birdie Reed of Fullerton. Child care will be provided. For 
information, call (714) 646-4652. 
</P>
<P>
Temple Eilat of Mission Viejo has been awarded the Whizin Institute for Jewish 
Family Life Dissemination Grant by the University of Judaism. Rabbi Bradley S. 
Artson and education director Andrea Raizen will participate in an intensive 
summer institute at the University of Judaism focusing on "Educating the 
Family." Temple Eilat is located at 22081 Hidalgo, Mission Viejo. For 
information, call (714) 770-9606. 
</P>
<P>
The Rev. Charles A. Endter, senior pastor at Our Redeemer Lutheran Church, 
12301 Magnolia Ave., Garden Grove, concludes his 34 years of ministry this 
month. Endter held his first worship on May 6, 1956, in the white frame 
building of the Presbyterian Church in Westminster. The congregation moved to 
temporary facilities on Lampson Avenue in 1957 and then to its current location 
in 1961. Endter will conclude his official acts by conducting a wedding on June 
30. For information, call (714) 539-9541. 
</P>
<P>
The Choir of St. Mark Presbyterian Church will present its second annual Pops 
Concert on Sunday at 7 p.m. The program features music from Broadway musicals, 
including "Carousel," "Phantom of the Opera," "A Chorus Line" and "Paint Your 
Wagon." Donations of $5 per person or $15 per family will benefit the Mary 
Magdalene Project, a residential program that helps women leave prostitution. 
The church is at 2100 Mar Vista Drive, Newport Beach. For information, call 
(714) 644-1341. 
</P>
<P>
The Rev. Bruce Larson will be installed as co-pastor of the Crystal Cathedral 
by the Rev. Robert H. Schuller on Sunday at both the 9 and 11 a.m. services at 
12141 Lewis St., Garden Grove. Larson has served as pastor of the University 
Presbyterian Church in Seattle, Wash., since 1980. He received his Master of 
Divinity degree from Seattle Pacific University. Larson will begin his ministry 
by delivering a series of messages Sunday through August on how to conquer 
life's fears. For information, call (714) 971-4068. 
</P>
<P>
Hugh Ross, a Christian apologist and noted astrophysicist who in recent weeks 
has spoken before the Soviet Academy of Science and in several Moscow 
universities, will talk about his experiences at Grace Church during Sunday's 9 
and 10:45 a.m. services and at a special 6 p.m. service. The Soviet speaking 
engagement allowed Ross the opportunity to present a Christian, biblical 
perspective on selected areas of scientific inquiry to the Soviet scientists at 
the academy. Grace Church is located at 3021 Blume Drive, Los Alamitos. For 
information, call (714) 826-5032 or (213) 493-5613. 
</P>
<P>
Orange County Religion Notes is published on Saturdays. Send items at least two 
weeks before the event to Thuha Tran, Orange County Religion Notes, The Times, 
1375 Sunflower Ave., Costa Mesa, Calif. 92626. Telephone calls cannot be 
accepted. Because of space limitations, The Times cannot guarantee that all 
notices will be published. Items must include subject, telephone number, event 
date, time and exact address. 
</P>
</TEXT>
