<HEADLINE>
<P>
CROATIA DISCARDING ITS COMMUNIST SYMBOLS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
BELGRADE, Yugoslavia 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The nation's second-biggest republic, Croatia, has decided to drop all 
Communist symbols from its institutions, the newspaper Borba said Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
The state presidency in Croatia, where Communists were defeated last month in 
the first free elections since World War II, has approved draft amendments to 
drop "socialist" from the republic's name and to remove the Communist red star 
from its flag and coat of arms, the paper said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
